That's my problem. Moving on.

357
00:23:07,399 --> 00:23:08,679
The bedrooms are all ready.

358
00:23:08,747 --> 00:23:10,319
Thank you, Mabel. Have you seen Sabrina?

359
00:23:10,442 --> 00:23:11,686
I'm right here, Mom.

360
00:23:12,459 --> 00:23:13,470
Where's Sebastian?

361
00:23:13,543 --> 00:23:15,486
He missed the ferry, but he'll be here
for the cocktail party.

362
00:23:15,562 --> 00:23:17,635
-You all are working my last nerve.
-Relax.

363
00:23:17,707 --> 00:23:19,560
-Hey! Sweetie!
-Hi, Dad.

364
00:23:19,624 --> 00:23:22,050
So good to see you!

365
00:23:22,125 --> 00:23:24,644
All right, they'll be here any minute.
Go change.

366
00:23:24,715 --> 00:23:27,399
That sounded a little bit like,
"Go fetch."

367
00:23:28,205 --> 00:23:29,315
Dad, Mom is right.

368
00:23:29,386 --> 00:23:32,519
You need to make a good impression
on my future mother-in-law, okay?

369
00:23:32,587 --> 00:23:33,569
Absolutely, sweetie.

370
00:23:33,645 --> 00:23:34,986
Thanks, Dad.

371
00:23:37,229 --> 00:23:40,328
-That's them! They're here!
-Mom, how do I look?

372
00:23:40,395 --> 00:23:41,541
-Do I have anything in my teeth?
-Sabrina.

373
00:23:41,612 --> 00:23:43,718
-What about my nose?
-Sabrina, that is vile.

374
00:23:44,107 --> 00:23:45,418
Now, remember who you are.

375
00:23:45,806 --> 00:23:48,039
You are my angel.

376
00:23:51,885 --> 00:23:52,999
Hello.

377
00:23:54,573 --> 00:23:55,783
Claudine.

378
00:23:56,746 --> 00:23:59,368
-Geneva.
-Auntie! You made it!

379
00:24:01,265 --> 00:24:03,720
Look at you. You're beautiful.

380
00:24:05,036 --> 00:24:07,245
Why didn't you respond
to the wedding invitation?

381
00:24:07,855 --> 00:24:10,028
The mail on the island
is so unpredictable.

382
00:24:10,096 --> 00:24:11,589
Are there no phones on the island?

383
00:24:11,664 --> 00:24:13,124
-Claudie.
-Mom.

384
00:24:15,504 --> 00:24:16,648
Where are you staying?

385
00:24:16,783 --> 00:24:18,671
In Grand-Mère's old room, of course.

386
00:24:18,734 --> 00:24:21,036
-See? Room for me.
-Come on. I have so much to tell you!

387
00:24:21,102 --> 00:24:23,691
I can't wait to show you
what I bought you. It's see-through.

388
00:24:23,762 --> 00:24:25,615
-So, it's really a gift for Jason.
-And where is he?

389
00:24:25,678 --> 00:24:27,820
I need to see the man
who stole my little girl's heart.

390
00:24:27,888 --> 00:24:30,756
Auntie, you are going to love him.
First of all...

391
00:24:30,831 --> 00:24:35,535
Just bring 'em in here and drop 'em.
Drop 'em right here. Put it...

